      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Abu Ali Al Ashary, from Muhammad Bin Salim, from Ahmad Bin Al Nazar, from Amro Bin Shimr, from Jabir, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Al-Husayn<sup>asws</sup> Bin Ali<sup>asws</sup> was killed and upon him<sup>asws</sup> was a coat of dark <span class=\"iTxt\">Khazz</span>, so they found therein sixty three tears from the strikes with the sword, and the stabbings with the spear, or the shootings with the arrow’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "9. Abu Ali al-Ash‘ariy has narrated from Muhammad ibn Salim from Ahmad ibn al-Nadr from ‘Amr ibn Shamir from Jabir who has said the following: “Abu Ja‘far, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said that when al-Husayn, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, was murdered, he wore a dark color Jubbah (gown) of al-Khazz (garments made of skin or fur of an animal that lives in water). They found thirty-three torn spots in it because of being hit with sword, spears or shooting arrows.’” "
        ]
